"Motohira S., Morino H., Matsumoto Y., Tomozawa K., Uede M., Ozawa H., Ogihara T.","Development of mn-type lithium-ion batteries and study for a Pure electric buses applications",2010,"Electrochemistry","78","1",,"30","35",,,,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-77649202359&partnerID=40&md5=e07c7127647435d2e0fb2d70551c8eaf","Hokuriku Electric Power Company, 2-54 Hisakata, Toyama-shi, Toyama 930-0848, Japan; Chugai Ro Co., Ltd., 2-4 Chikko-Shinmachi, Nishi-ku, Sakai 592-8331, Japan; Enax. Co, Ltd., 11-19 Otowa 2, Bunkyo-ku, Tokyo 112-0013, Japan; University of Fukui, 9-1 Bunkyo 3, Fukui-shi, Fukui 910-8507, Japan","Motohira, S., Hokuriku Electric Power Company, 2-54 Hisakata, Toyama-shi, Toyama 930-0848, Japan, University of Fukui, 9-1 Bunkyo 3, Fukui-shi, Fukui 910-8507, Japan; Morino, H., Hokuriku Electric Power Company, 2-54 Hisakata, Toyama-shi, Toyama 930-0848, Japan; Matsumoto, Y., Hokuriku Electric Power Company, 2-54 Hisakata, Toyama-shi, Toyama 930-0848, Japan; Tomozawa, K., Chugai Ro Co., Ltd., 2-4 Chikko-Shinmachi, Nishi-ku, Sakai 592-8331, Japan; Uede, M., Chugai Ro Co., Ltd., 2-4 Chikko-Shinmachi, Nishi-ku, Sakai 592-8331, Japan; Ozawa, H., Enax. Co, Ltd., 11-19 Otowa 2, Bunkyo-ku, Tokyo 112-0013, Japan; Ogihara, T., University of Fukui, 9-1 Bunkyo 3, Fukui-shi, Fukui 910-8507, Japan","From the viewpoint of reducing carbon dioxide emissions, the practical use of electric buses has been expected to be one of the effective solutions to global warming. Even though lithium-ion batteries using lithium manganese oxide have been studied for use in electric vehicles, it is Still necessary to improve their characteristics such as energy density, maximum operating temperature and cycle performance. Manganese oxide lithium-ion batteries for an electric bus developed by internal-combustion spray pyrolysis methods and its performance in an actual road test have been studied. The performance of the electric bus was satisfactory; the bus could run for 74 km on a full charge.","Electric Bus; Energy Saving; Lithium-Ion Batteries; Spinel Type; Spray Pyrolysis","Carbon dioxide emissions; Cycle performance; Effective solution; Electric bus; Energy density; Lithium manganese oxide; Lithium-Ion Batteries; Lithium-ion battery; Operating temperature; Practical use; Road tests; Spinel-type; Spray pyrolysis method; Automobiles; Buses; Carbon dioxide; Electric vehicles; Energy conservation; Global warming; Ions; Lithium; Lithium alloys; Lithium batteries; Lithium compounds; Manganese; Manganese oxide; Spray pyrolysis",,,,,,"Yamasaki, K., Fukuda, M., Nojima, T., Taniguchi, S., (2000) Proc. of the 2000 Japan Industry Applications Society Conference, 1, p. 349. , in Japanese; Ozawa, H., Ogihara, T., Ozawa, K., (2008) Electrochemistry, 3, p. 76; Gao, Y., Reimers, J.N., Dahn, J.R., (1996) Phys. Rev. B., 54, p. 3878; Yamada, A., Tanaka, M., (1995) Mater. Res. Bull., 30, p. 715; De Kock, A., Ferg, E., Gummow, R.J., (1998) J. Power Sources, 70, p. 247; Gummow, R.J., De Kock, A., Thackeray, M.M., (1994) Solid State Ionics, 69, p. 59; Mukoyama, I., Myojin, K., Ogihara, T., Uede, M., Ozawa, H., Ozawa, K., (2006) Key Eng. Mater., 320, p. 251; Myojin, K., Ogihara, T., Ogata, N., Aoyagi, N., Aikiyo, H., Ookawa, T., Omura, S., Oohara, T., (2004) Adv. Power Technol., 15, p. 397; Motohira, S., Ogihara, T., Mukoyama, I., Nakamura, T., Ozawa, H., Fujii, K., Uede, M., Morino, H., (2007) WEVA J., 1, p. 165; Motohira, S., Morino, H., Matsumoto, Y., Ogihara, T., (2007) Proc. of the 2007 Japan Industry Applications Society Conference, 2, p. 181. , in Japanese","Motohira, S.; Hokuriku Electric Power Company, 2-54 Hisakata, Toyama-shi, Toyama 930-0848, Japan",,,,,,,,13443542,,EECTF,,"English","Electrochem",Article,Scopus,2-s2.0-77649202359
